2
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:42,071
"and brought you unto Myself..."

3
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:44,953
Torah - Exodus - chapter XIX - 4

4
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:50,839
<i>They had been forgotten</i>
<i>on their mountaintops</i>

5
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:52,388
<i>near Gondar.</i>

6
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:55,792
<i>Yet, since the dawn of time,</i>

7
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:59,431
<i>the Ethiopian Jews,</i>
<i>known as the "Falashas",</i>

8
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:03,150
<i>dreamed of returning</i>
<i>to their homeland, the Holy Land,</i>

9
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,072
<i>Jerusalem.</i>

10
00:01:13,320 --> 00:01:15,390
<i>1984.</i>

11
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,031
<i>With Israeli and U.S. Aid,</i>

12
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:22,119
<i>a vast program was undertaken</i>
<i>from November to January 1985</i>

13
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:24,915
<i>to transport the Ethiopian Jews</i>
<i>to Israel.</i>

14
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:27,750
<i>The Falashas were returned</i>

15
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:31,190
<i>and finally recognized</i>
<i>as descendants of King Solomon</i>

16
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:34,835
<i>and the Queen of Sheba.</i>

17
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,917
<i>The Israeli secret service</i>

18
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:40,998
<i>carried out the operation</i>
<i>on the sly,</i>

19
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:43,237
<i>keeping it from the Mengitsu</i>

20
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:47,148
<i>pro-Soviet regime who had</i>
<i>prohibited their emigration.</i>

21
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:51,393
<i>The Falashas walked from Ethiopia</i>
<i>to Sudan,</i>

22
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,673
<i>a Muslim country under Charia law.</i>

23
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:58,988
<i>There, they had to hide their</i>
<i>Jewish identity under pain of death</i>

24
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:03,795
<i>In Sudan, planes awaited</i>
<i>to take them to Israel.</i>

25
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:07,552
<i>On the road,</i>
<i>hundreds died of sickness,</i>

26
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:11,639
<i>famine, exhaustion.</i>
<i>Others were killed by bandits.</i>

27
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:14,516
<i>In the 1980s,</i>

28
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,276
<i>the Sudanese camps welcomed</i>

29
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:22,598
<i>thousands of Africans from 26</i>
<i>countries who were prey to famine:</i>

30
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:25,069
<i>Christians, Muslims,</i>

31
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,796
<i>and clandestine Jews.</i>

32
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:32,950
<i>The first secret airlift operation,</i>
<i>known as "Operation Moses",</i>

33
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,833
<i>saved 8,000 Ethiopian Jews.</i>

34
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:37,868
<i>4,000</i>

35
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,753
<i>died on the road</i>
<i>between Ethiopia and Sudan,</i>

36
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:43,994
<i>murdered, tortured</i>

37
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,999
<i>or suffering from famine,</i>
<i>thirst and exhaustion.</i>

38
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:51,948
<i>Many children reached the Holy</i>
<i>Land alone or as orphans.</i>

39
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:07,392
