Let me.

85
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:11,238
Like this.

86
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:52,748
Enjoy your meal.

87
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,559
Fork.

88
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,919
Like this.

89
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,993
Silence!

90
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:25,158
Silence, please!

91
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:31,316
For the first time our black brothers
have been brought out of Africa,

92
00:15:35,280 --> 00:15:37,271
not to be sold

93
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:40,032
or made slaves,

94
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,956
but to be saved,

95
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,518
liberated!

96
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:50,788
Welcome!

97
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:06,070
On behalf of my entire community,
I thank Israel

98
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:11,953
for having helped us
return to Jerusalem,

99
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:16,036
and for having saved us.

100
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,315
What's his name?

101
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:24,638
- Adisalem.
- That's not a Jewish name.

102
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,474
Yes it is.

103
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:30,315
Adis means "new",
and alem means "world".

104
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:33,314
Adisalem means "new world".

105
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,397
We'll call him Eddy.

106
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,993
Write it: Eddy.

107
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,558
Are you sure you're Jewish?

108
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,836
I'll ask you one last time.

109
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,835
I personally don't believe it.

110
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:06,157
Nobody knows you here.

111
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:08,111
What village are you from?

112
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,559
Have you forgotten?

113
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:13,309
What is your grandfather's name?
And your great grandfather?

114
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:15,398
Can't you remember?

115
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:18,834
Follow me.

116
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:21,353
Come on.

117
