your brother, Yakov,

123
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:45,998
and your sister, Aster.

124
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:49,073
They all died on the road to Sudan.

125
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,789
The name of our village is Weleka.

126
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:53,669
Repeat.

127
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:57,157
My name is Solomon,
my cow's name was Mandala.

128
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:00,039
No, just Solomon, not the cow!

129
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:03,156
Are you circumcised?

130
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:07,393
I believe you.

131
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:10,874
Is this your son?

132
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:15,079
What's his name?

133
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,389
Solomon!

134
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:18,591
Solomon... Schlomo.

135
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,676
"Schlomo", do you understand?

136
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:28,433
Your father and your grandfather?

137
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:31,756
We're from Weleka.

138
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:34,674
Everyone knows us here.

139
00:18:35,040 --> 00:18:37,349
Qes Amhra, too.

140
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:40,109
My husband's name was Isaac,

141
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,914
my daughter, Aster,

142
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:46,554
my youngest son, Yakov.

143
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:49,513
They're all dead.

144
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:53,914
Solomon is all I have left.

145
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,079
Schlomo.

146
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:00,109
Would you like to go to school,
Schlomo?

147
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,634
Of course!

148
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:04,359
With her!

149
00:19:05,520 --> 00:19:08,034
You'll stay together. Don't worry.

150
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:45,075
Through there. They come in and out.
There's a door!

151
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:49,396
There are a lot of them.

152
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:12,669
She's getting better.

153
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:15,077
She's in good hands now.

154
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,591
You can see her later.

155
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:21,437
Take off your coat.

156
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:32,794
Do you want to watch TV?

157
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:58,838
Nobody came out of the TV.

158
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:01,554
They haven't gone to bed yet.

159
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:05,630
Keep your secret.

160
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:10,358
Don't say a word to anybody...

161
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,833
Never.

162
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:16,709
Otherwise, they'll send you
back to Ethiopia.

163
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:19,473
You are my son,

164
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,436
a Jew from Weleka.

165
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:26,558
Learn our traditions.

166
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,950
That way you'll be safe.

167
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:35,316
Don't forget the names of your
parents and your grandparents.

168
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:38,359
Isaac,

169
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,309
Hana,

170
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:42,388
Yakov,

171
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:44,832
Sura.

172
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:49,355
And don't forget your mother

173
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:53,158
who is still over there.

174
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:55,350
Never!

175
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:01,313
One day, you'll see her again.

176
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:16,631
Because you'll live!

177
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:24,919
Don't die.

178
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:28,112
Don't cry.

179
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:02,199
Hello, children.

180
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:05,315
I'm the director of the school...

181
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:35,438
Hello, my name's Zwi.
What's your name?

182
00:24:49,040 --> 00:24:51,793
Schlomo,
I'm the school psychiatrist...

183
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,119
Cow.

184
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:28,239
Girl.

185
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:30,675
Boy.

186
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:33,358
Bird.

187
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:36,238
Hat.

188
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:38,954
Fish.

189
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:41,679
Watch.

190
00:25:42,360 --> 00:25:43,509
Banana.

191
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:46,433
Sit down.

192
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:49,993
Hello, everybody.

193
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:55,036
Do any children
have family still left

194
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,798
in Ethiopia or Sudan?

195
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:20,630
You're gonna eat this!

196
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:24,277
Eat, I say!

197
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:28,196
Stop! Have you lost your minds?

198
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:29,469
Let him go!

199
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:35,398
It'll be OK.

200
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:47,555
No!

201
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:50,911
It's not my fault!

202
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:00,749
Mommy,

203
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:03,396
I have to become like them.

204
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:05,590
I don't want to change.

205
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:08,315
How will you recognize me?

206
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:11,718
Please, let me come home...

207
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:19,435
Well?

208
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:20,709
Can't find him.

209
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:23,116
I've had it.
This kid's driving me nuts.

210
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:25,677
Not in the park or the rooms.

211
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:27,711
We've woken everyone.
I've called the police.

212
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:30,068
Come on.

213
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:43,034
Schlomo, stop!

214
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:56,313
Leave him alone.
He's just a child. Leave him!

215
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:10,756
12 kilometers on foot!

216
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:12,592
- He's only 9 years old.
- This child...

217
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:16,713
He learns Hebrew quickly
and is very interested in school.

218
00:28:17,160 --> 00:28:20,516
I see his violence,
but we've got to give him some time.

219
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:22,671
I want a solution now.

220
