He needs a stricter school
that will control him better.

221
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:28,392
Maybe Echel Avraham.

222
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:30,318
Is there any surviving
family member?

223
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:33,557
Nobody from his old village
wants him.

224
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:37,395
Do you have any ideas? Tell me!

225
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:39,358
Schlomo ran away, barefoot,

226
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:40,515
wrapped in a sheet.

227
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:42,676
Which way did he go? Which way?

228
00:28:42,800 --> 00:28:44,836
Towards the south, Ethiopia.

229
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:46,918
Why?

230
00:28:47,120 --> 00:28:49,873
Maybe he's trying
to return to his old life,

231
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,468
with his mother and family.

232
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:55,355
Time and another school
will never bring

233
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:59,479
Schlomo's mother and family back.

234
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:01,439
It's impossible.

235
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:02,675
I understand.

236
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:05,076
That's fine. Thanks.

237
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:16,234
Come in, please.

238
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:23,756
Schlomo, your adoptive parents,

239
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:26,991
Yael and Yoram Harrari.

240
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:41,549
112 horsepower, automatic,

241
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:44,878
it can go up to 200 km/h.

242
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,916
Volvo, the best car in the world.

243
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:50,476
Do you like cars, Schlomo?

244
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:56,195
You can call us "daddy"
and "mommy", if you want.

245
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:06,117
This is your brother and sister:

246
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:07,912
Tali and Dany.

247
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:26,839
Look, the stadium!

248
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:31,476
You can come and run here
if you want. I'll sign you up.

249
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:38,359
You like to run, don't you?

250
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:08,358
Gramps, they're here.
Come and see.

251
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:11,389
They're here. Daddy, daddy!

252
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:21,159
Hello, my cherubs.

253
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:23,999
Not a word about his
dead parents, okay?

254
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:26,913
This is Schlomo.

255
00:31:27,440 --> 00:31:28,793
This is Tali,

256
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:31,598
Dany... and Gramps.

257
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,518
Yoram's father.

258
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:36,754
You're a polite boy.

259
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:40,350
We never looked somebody in the eye
where I grew up either.

260
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:41,959
He grew up in Egypt.

261
00:31:42,120 --> 00:31:43,997
- Near Ethiopia.
- That's all you have?

262
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:47,197
What, I didn't say anything
about his dead parents!

263
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,793
Your room.

264
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:51,797
It was mine before.

265
00:31:57,880 --> 00:32:00,917
You can put whatever you want
on the walls.

266
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:06,156
I forgot the presents!

267
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:08,472
Right... the presents.

