331
00:37:19,040 --> 00:37:21,713
Did you have a good day, darling?

332
00:37:41,720 --> 00:37:43,631
Hello, Mrs. Zilbermann.

333
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,435
How are you?

334
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:47,795
So, so...

335
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:50,874
I've brought you
some fish and oranges.

336
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:52,275
What?

337
00:37:52,440 --> 00:37:54,317
Fish and oranges!

338
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:56,511
And the brownie?

339
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:58,358
I forgot!

340
00:37:58,520 --> 00:38:00,033
Next week.

341
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:02,593
I'll take down the garbage.

342
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:04,551
Thanks a lot.

343
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:06,554
Bye-bye!

344
00:38:06,680 --> 00:38:08,159
Take care of yourself!

345
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:34,311
Where did we receive the Torah?

346
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:39,951
- On Mount Sinai.
- Exactly!

347
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:45,719
And who brought us the Torah?

348
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:50,948
Moses.

349
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:52,993
Very good.

350
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:10,476
Who is the founder of our religion?

351
00:39:12,680 --> 00:39:13,795
Jesus!

352
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:24,636
Because... Jesus...

353
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:27,560
converted... he... first Jew...

354
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:30,354
who became a Christian...
Christianity...

355
00:39:30,480 --> 00:39:31,993
He suffered...

356
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:34,350
And that's why he walked on water,

357
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:37,712
turned the other cheek... got a slap.

358
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:42,157
And Jesus thought...
God's only child,

359
00:39:43,160 --> 00:39:46,118
but... so nice
to have brothers and sisters.

360
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:51,758
And his mother... is his mother,

361
00:39:52,080 --> 00:39:54,514
but Jesus mustn't say a word...

362
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:07,598
"Genesis".

363
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:14,949
"In the beginning
there was heaven and earth..."

364
00:40:26,720 --> 00:40:30,235
One morning I'll wake up,
and I'll be all white.

365
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:34,196
And I'll speak Yiddish
like a real Jew.

366
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:36,158
Like Mrs. Zilbermann,

367
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:38,077
from the first floor,

368
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:41,715
who's losing her hair
and has a hard time getting around.

369
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:46,837
Her feet have swollen up
these past few weeks.

370
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:49,754
I buy her milk and bread.

371
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:54,274
And brownies. She loves them.

372
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:58,193
She's constantly saying:
"Oy, oy, oy, mein Gott!"

373
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:01,714
That's what it is to be Jewish!

374
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:04,675
Mother's Day

375
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:35,355
Is Yael OK?

376
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:36,993
Yes, don't worry.

377
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:39,754
You're not happy it's me?

378
00:41:41,760 --> 00:41:43,591
Sorry, you're not happy?

379
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:45,159
I understand French.

380
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:46,958
Okay... okay.

381
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:49,398
Was school OK?

382
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:53,117
I have a surprise for you.

383
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:56,230
Do you understand "surprise"?

384
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,597
There are good and bad ones...

385
00:41:58,960 --> 00:42:00,712
and big and little surprises.

386
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:02,679
I have a good one!

387
00:42:10,080 --> 00:42:12,230
Yoram, it's broke!

388
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:15,476
- What did you touch?
- Me, no!

389
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:17,352
It's not a toy, damn it!

390
00:42:17,560 --> 00:42:18,629
You say play.

391
00:42:18,760 --> 00:42:21,320
I didn't say to fiddle with it.
How can I work now?

392
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:24,873
I don't know what he did.
He broke it!

393
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:29,955
Does it work?

394
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:31,439
Of course it works!

395
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:34,190
Your father's got a bug
sometimes.

396
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:37,232
There are too many pieces
to change inside.

397
00:42:37,440 --> 00:42:39,670
Murad Khelfi,
our computer genius.

398
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:41,558
A pillar of our company.

399
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:43,468
Schlomo, I suppose.

400
00:42:44,120 --> 00:42:46,156
He can't stop talking about you.

401
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:50,754
Listen, if they ever seriously
get on your nerves,

402
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:53,440
you can come and stay at my place.

403
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:55,068
OK?

404
00:42:58,920 --> 00:43:02,037
When the Queen of Sheba,
your great, great, great-grandmother,

405
00:43:02,160 --> 00:43:04,355
crossed Egypt for Ethiopia

406
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:06,710
after her meeting with King Solomon,

407
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:11,275
I could've shut the door
and never let her pass.

408
00:43:11,880 --> 00:43:13,950
She was beautiful, you know.

409
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:18,117
I could've taken advantage.
But I didn't.

410
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,553
Do you know why?

411
00:43:21,320 --> 00:43:24,790
I wanted to meet you.
I wanted you to exist.

412
00:43:27,320 --> 00:43:29,709
- What do you say to Grandpa?
- Thank you.

413
00:43:33,480 --> 00:43:37,234
You tell me how I became a Jew.

414
00:43:37,600 --> 00:43:41,639
But I'm not telling you how
you got out of that dump Alexandria.

415
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:42,949
Dump?

416
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:44,749
Where did you get that?

417
00:43:44,920 --> 00:43:46,433
Alexandria, a dump?

418
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:48,353
Heathen, ignoramus!

419
00:43:48,480 --> 00:43:51,472
Black savage! Baboon!
Come here so I can slug you.

420
00:43:51,680 --> 00:43:54,558
The largest library in the world
you call a dump!

421
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:03,879
For you.

422
00:44:06,920 --> 00:44:08,672
I can't read Amharic.

423
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:11,319
You'll learn.

424
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:18,117
Can I talk to you please?

425
00:44:19,240 --> 00:44:21,834
Schlomo, could you leave us alone?

426
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:23,395
Thanks.

427
00:44:24,320 --> 00:44:28,154
This is a bit embarrassing, but...

428
00:44:28,280 --> 00:44:30,794
Parents want to withdraw
their kids from school

429
00:44:30,920 --> 00:44:32,990
if Schlomo isn't transferred.

430
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:35,510
They're afraid the level
will go down.

431
00:44:35,640 --> 00:44:38,393
I know it's wrong,
Schlomo has very good marks.

432
00:44:42,040 --> 00:44:45,919
And they're afraid
of diseases from Africa.

433
00:44:47,080 --> 00:44:48,069
I know that...

434
00:44:54,840 --> 00:44:57,593
Listen, you morons!

435
00:44:57,720 --> 00:44:58,835
I've had enough!

436
00:44:58,960 --> 00:45:02,430
My son is the most beautiful child
in the world. Understand?

437
00:45:02,680 --> 00:45:05,558
He's as good,
if not better than your children!

438
00:45:08,360 --> 00:45:10,920
He's healthy as can be.
Tell them!

439
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:17,628
His pimples? It's stress!

440
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:20,673
You're not the first or the only ones
to give him a hard time!

441
00:45:22,320 --> 00:45:24,311
He's healthy! He's healthy!

442
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:36,635
Schlomo won't budge from this school.

443
00:45:37,480 --> 00:45:39,198
You fucking idiots!

444
00:45:48,400 --> 00:45:51,358
- Tigress, can you lick my pimples?
- Stupid!

445
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:56,354
Stop thinking about it.
You did the right thing.

446
00:45:56,760 --> 00:45:58,910
Let him handle it on his own.

447
00:46:00,680 --> 00:46:02,636
He knows we love him.

448
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:04,910
Let him go to school on his own.

449
00:46:05,760 --> 00:46:08,399
- He's only 9.
- Dany's 8. He goes on his own.

450
00:46:08,520 --> 00:46:11,592
Let him be,
otherwise they'll make fun of him.

451
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:14,111
Let them respect him, not you!

452
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:30,479
Dany, put out the glasses.

453
00:47:30,960 --> 00:47:32,109
I haven't finished.

454
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:36,155
Are you OK, darling?

455
00:47:37,960 --> 00:47:40,679
Can you handle this?
I've a meeting tomorrow.

456
00:47:40,800 --> 00:47:41,835
What is it?

457
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:43,672
Hello, my love.

458
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:56,912
Tomorrow you have a medical exam
with the immigration service.

459
00:47:57,640 --> 00:47:59,596
We leave for Jerusalem at 7:30.

460
00:48:00,160 --> 00:48:02,628
We're getting up early.
So get to sleep.

461
00:48:37,440 --> 00:48:38,429
Ready to go?

462
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:40,790
Eat something. We have to go.

463
00:48:41,160 --> 00:48:42,559
In 15 minutes, understood?

464
00:48:42,800 --> 00:48:44,279
Dany, get up!

465
00:49:04,040 --> 00:49:05,359
Are you cold?

466
00:49:07,000 --> 00:49:09,036
